<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,663,1049]" box="[264,558,663,688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[264,558,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Comments and diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,663,1049]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
The characteristics mentioned in the key are valuable for the recognition of 
<taxonomicName box="[1219,1315,703,729]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Agapostemoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hurdi">
<emphasis box="[1219,1237,703,728]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1253,1315,703,728]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">hurdi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially the low occipital carina, not lamellate dorsally, and the sparse punctation on lateral portions of the disc of T 
<number box="[640,652,783,809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
. Other features of this species are the clypeal punctures, separated by several times their diameters; the tegula transparent brown, often metallic anteromedially; fore leg with coxa metallic laterally, external surface of trochanter, femur and tibia dark amber; hindleg femur with a conspicuous posteroventral tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,663,1049]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts" box="[312,611,943,969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" refString="Roberts, R. B. &amp; Brooks, R. W. (1987) Agapostemonine bees of Mesoamerica (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 53 (7), 357 - 392." type="journal article" year="1987">
Roberts &amp; Brooks (
<number box="[542,603,943,969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
called attention to the female color morphs in 
<taxonomicName box="[1166,1261,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Agapostemoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hurdi">
<emphasis box="[1166,1261,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">A. hurdi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female T 
<number box="[374,388,983,1009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
­T 
<date box="[415,491,983,1009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<number box="[415,430,983,1009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="4.0">4</number>
may
</date>
be either black or amber, in both cases also with yellow transverse bands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
